<HEADLINE> Bonn Surprised by Iran's Confirmation of German </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 10 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus
Kinkel Saturday said that he was shocked at an Iranian appeal
court's ruling to uphold the death sentence passed on a German
businessman for having sexual relations with a Moslem woman.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Saturday in Bonn, Kinkel said that the
decision made by the Iranian court went against all expectations
of the German government, which has been trying to negotiate an
acquittal for the 56-year-old German businessman identified as
Helmut Hofer.
</P>
<P>
Kinkel also said he had summoned the Iranian ambassador to the
German Foreign Ministry to receive a formal protest from Bonn.
</P>
<P>
"Today's confirmation of the death sentence against Helmut
Hofer will inevitably cast a shadow over the wish of both sides to
improve relations," Kinkel said.
</P>
<P>
Hofer's defense lawyer also announced that he would appeal
again to the Iranian highest court against the death penalty which
was first handed down by an Iranian court at the end of January.
</P>
</TEXT>
