<HEADLINE> Tanzanian PM to Visit Germany, Thailand, Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian Prime Minister
Frederick Sumaye will leave here Sunday to start a trip of
Germany, Thailand and Japan to promote ties with the three
nations, according to a Foreign Ministry statement Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sumaye will visit Munich, Germany during October 11-14. After
that, he will pay an official visit to Thailand from October 15
to 18, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister will then fly to Japan to attend the Tokyo
International Conference on Africa Development, the Foreign
Ministry statement said.
</P>
<P>
Sumaye will also visit Kagoshima in the Kyushu District in
Japan to open the Asia-Africa Symposium 1998 organized by the
Karamosia Organization.
</P>
<P>
Before winding up his trip, the prime minister will visit and
send condolences to the family of Rieko Hanaoka, a Japanese
medical technician who was killed by bandits last month in Dar es
Salaam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
