<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Physical Society Set up in Addis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Physical
Society was established here Saturday with an aim to enhance
scientific study and research in this east African country.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizing committee, the society was set up
to consolidate physics education and exchange of scientific
information in the country.
</P>
<P>
It also aims to extend cooperation and communication between
the society and similar national, regional and international
societies.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the inaugural meeting at the Addis Ababa
University, Ethiopian Science and Technology Commissioner Asrat
Bulbula said special attention should be given to such societies
as the Ethiopian Physical Society.
</P>
<P>
Habtamu Zewdie, associate dean of the science faculty of the
Addis Ababa University, said the number of physics professionals
in Africa, including Ethiopia, is insignificant because much of
the attention and assistance has been directed to subjects
related to immediate food needs. 
</P>
