<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Congratulates Yemen on Hanish Islands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia on Saturday
expressed congratulation to Yemen on the ruling of international
arbitration on Yemen's right to sovereignty over Hanish
archipelago.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Crown Prince and Deputy Prime Minister Abdullah Ibn
Abdul-Aziz contacted by telephone on Saturday the Yemeni President
Ali Abdullah Saleh and sent the congratulation, the Saudi Press
Agency (SPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The London-based International Arbitration Committee (IAC)
ruled Friday in favor of Yemen in its dispute with Eritrea over
the Red Sea Islands of Hanish.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah is now spending a private vacation in Hawaii of the
United States.
</P>
<P>
During the call, the Crown Prince also reviewed bilateral
relations with the Yemeni President and the latest developments of
the Arab, regional and international arenas, the SPA said. But it
didn't elaborate.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia and Yemen have their own land disputes. On July
19, a dispute over the Red Sea Island of Duwaima, claimed by both
Riyadh and Sana'a, led to an armed confrontation between the two
Arab neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Since then, several rounds of high-level talks have been held
between Saudi Arabia and Yemen on ways to resolve the crisis
resulting from the armed clashes, which claimed lives of three
Yemeni soldiers .
</P>
<P>
Both sides have agreed to do their utmost to prevent further
clashes on the island and other disputed areas. 
</P>
