<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-10 20:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AL Hails Settlement of Hanish Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League (AL) Secretariat
Saturday expressed welcome to the ruling of international
arbitration on Yemen's right to sovereignty over Hanish
archipelago.
</P>
<P>
AL Assistant Secretary General Hamed Ben Holei said the league
considers such achievement in settling borderline disputes as a
model for solving problems between neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
He mentioned Egypt's efforts that have contributed to reaching
a satisfactory solution to both parties along with endeavors by
France and the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Holei, in the name of the AL Secretariat, congratulated Yemen
and Eritrea for such civilized way of solving borderline problems.
</P>
<P>
The ruling was taken Friday by the London-based International
Court of Arbitration.
</P>
<P>
Yemeni Prime Minister Abdul-Karim al-Iryani described the
international arbitration decision to restore the Red Sea Hanish
islands to Yemen's sovereignty as a momentous victory for Yemeni
and Arab diplomacy.
</P>
<P>
In December 1995, the Red Sea navigation movement was at stake
following the flare-up of an acute crisis between Yemen and
Eritrea, with growing fears of a large-scale military
confrontation.
</P>
<P>
In mid-December, the Eritrean troops captured the three Red Sea
islands of Hanish after a war of word with Yemen in which both
countries claimed sovereignty over the strategic islands.
</P>
<P>
After a diplomatic drive, Yemen and Eritrea accepted
international arbitration to decide the ownership of the islands.
</P>
<P>
Eventually, the two countries signed an agreement in Paris in
May 1996 under which they accepted taking the case to London's
International Court of Arbitration.
</P>
<P>
The Permanent Court of Arbitration ruled Friday that the
disputed islands in the Red Sea were partly the sovereign
territory of Yemen and partly the sovereign territory of Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
The arbitration decision will be implemented within 90 days. In
a statement issued from its Hague registry, the tribunal awarded
Eritrea the Mohabbakah islands, some of the Haycock Islands and
the South West Rocks. Yemen gained sovereignty of the Zuqar-Hanish
group, the island of Jaba al-Tayr and the Zubayr group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981011.0029 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-10 20:37 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Spokesman Denies Upholding Death Sentence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Ministry
spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi on Saturday denied the report that an
Iranian appeals court has upheld the death sentence on German
businessman Helmut Hofer.
</P>
<P>
"So far no new verdict has been issued on Hofer," the official
news agency IRNA quoted Mohammadi as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, the morning daily Iran affiliated to IRNA reported on
Saturday that an Iranian appeals court has upheld the death
sentence on Hofer for having an affair with a Muslim woman.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi said that Hofer was sentenced to death by a local
court, but after Hofer appealed the verdict, Iran's supreme court
found some problems with verdict and sent back the case to the
original court.
</P>
<P>
The original court removed the problems and returned the case
to the supreme court, he said, some press misunderstood the issue
and termed it as a new verdict on Hofer.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi also said that Hofer's case is ready for the appeals
court to review and Hofer and his lawyer have been informed of
the procedure.
</P>
<P>
Hofer was arrested at Tehran international airport in
September last year with a 26-year-old Iranian woman on grounds
of sexual relations and was sentenced to death by an Iranian
court in January.
</P>
<P>
According to the Iranian laws, non-Muslim man is forbidden to
have sexual relations with a Muslim woman.
</P>
<P>
Hofer's case has aroused Germany's concern and senior German
officials have warned that the relations between Tehran and Bonn
would be seriously affected if the death sentence on Hofer is
carried out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
