<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 11 (Xinhua)-- Underachievers of China soccer
had to continue their struggle against demotion after the 24th
round league competition on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan Hongjinlong failed to grab three points at home court to
inspire themselves in their bid to avoid delegation after being
forced to a 0-0 tie by the Chinese Army, another club fighting
for last straw.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen Ping'an fought hard to level with Qingdao Hainiu two
times although this could only count as a cold comfort for they
still had to confront the strong possibility of being relegated.
</P>
<P>
