downed 1-2 by Guangzhou Apollo at bottom whose relegation seemed
to a sure bet.
</P>
<P>
Shandong Luneng could breathe more easily after they cruised
to a 2-1 home victory over Shanghai Shenhua, which almost made
certain their staying in the first division competition next
season.
</P>
<P>
Dalian Wanda kept their unstoppable winning momentum as they
thrashed Yanbian Aodong 3-1 when they set two records in China
league history.
</P>
<P>
Hao Haidong expanded his scoring record to 18 in a season to
beat the former 17 in top scoring list as Wanda extended their
winning streak to 11 in a season, one more than the former record
of 10 set by Shanghai Shenhua in 1995.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Sichuan Quanxing trounced Guangzhou Songri
4-0. Beijing Guo'an destroyed Vanguards Huangdao 2-0. 
