<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Rises to 8.69 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 11 (Xinhua) -- The annual rate of inflation
in India continued its upward trend and touched 8.69 percent for
the week that ended on September 26 from 8.55 percent the previous
week, according to official figures Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sustained increases in prices of food articles and food
products, especially vegetables and edible oils, pushed up the
inflation rate to its second-highest levels in three years during
the week under review.
</P>
<P>
Inflation was at a record low of 3.47 percent in the
corresponding week last year. 
</P>
