<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China in Support of Small, Medium-sized Enterprise Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, October 11 (Xinhua ) -- China has introduced
wide-ranging measures to support the development of small- to
medium-sized enterprises and transform them into an important
force for propelling the nation's economic and social progress.
</P>
<P>
Dai Guiying, an official with State Development Planning
Commission, said that the Chinese Government plans to set up a
fair investment and fund-raising system to increase funding
channels for related enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Dai is currently in the port city of Yantai to attend the
ongoing second APEC Small- and Medium-sized Enterprise Technology
Exchange and Exhibition Fair which will run through October 14.
</P>
<P>
The central government will continue to increase funding for
infrastructure construction and basic industries in order to
create an improved environment beneficial to the growth of the
small to medium-sized enterprises, he said, adding that it will
also provide more guidance and help promote the development of
related enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Dai said, the government is revising the "Law on
Rural and Township Industries" and drafting the "Law on
Revitalizing Small- and Medium-Sized Enterprises". The new laws
will ensure fair enterprise competition and protect legitimate
rights of small- and medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to encourage the growth of intermediary
organizations serving small- to medium-sized enterprises and
advance the transformation of scientific and technological
achievements into productive forces. China's technological markets
recorded a 1997 business volume of 35 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The nation's 10 registered small- to medium-sized ventures,
which account for 99 percent of the total number of enterprises,
contribute 60 percent of the total industrial output value and 40
percent of pre-tax profits. They also provide 75 percent of the
total number of job opportunities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
