<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heart Transplanting Success In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Lin Qizhong, 13, who
underwent successful heart transplant surgery on September 8, has
been released from the the hospital.
</P>
<P>
Lin, the son of a farmer in east China's Fujian Province,
suffered from serious heart defects and was admitted to the Daping
Hospital, an affiliate unit of the PLA Third Military Medical
University in southwest China's Chongqing Municipality, on
September 1.
</P>
<P>
Surgeons determined a transplant represented the only way to
save the youngster's life. Lin received the heart transplant one
week later, with the donor organ coming from a 28-year old victim
declared brain-dead by doctors.
</P>
<P>
Doctors conducted a thorough and careful physical examination
on October 8 and gave Lin a clean bill of health. Lin has returned
home and resumed the life of a normal young man his age.
</P>
<P>
Lin is China's youngest heart transplant patient, with experts
noting the promising prospects for him to enjoy a productive life.
</P>
</TEXT>
