his gun and fired a shot, said SAPA.
</P>
<P>
Party supporters scurried for cover with some rushing to
protect Mosisili and his deputy Kelebone Maope.
</P>
<P>
The LCD leadership immediately blamed the political opposition
parties for the shooting incident. They said the youths were sent
to assassinate Mosisili and Maope.
</P>
<P>
About 5,000 supporters, who had turned out to listen to the
LCD leadership, have started dispersing.
</P>
<P>
A group of armed youths were beaten by supporters after being
spotted in the crowd, LCD officials said.
</P>
<P>
The youths are alleged to have been driven to the rally in a
Toyota Venture.
</P>
<P>
One of them was arrested and was being questioned.
</P>
<P>
The opposition alliance dismissed LCD claims as "nonsensical",
saying they were just a smear campaign against the alliance.
</P>
<P>
"THis is absolute trash. We are not assassins like them and
have sent no one to kill Mosisili and his bunch," alliance
spokesman Vincent Malebo said. 
