<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Local government elections began
in Greece on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
About 8.9 million voters have registered for the elections, the
first since the extensive re-drawing of the local government map
and merger of small communities into larger municipal units.
</P>
<P>
For the first time, citizens of the European Union (EU)
residing in Greece can vote in the elections. Among the 8.9
million voters, 1,468 are citizens of other EU member states.
