<HEADLINE> Shandong Opens Inscribed Tablet Exhibition Hall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, October 11 (Xinhua) -- An inscribed tablet exhibition
hall recently opened in Qufu, the home of Confucius.
</P>
<P>
The garden hall, which is located in the former palaces of
Confucius, covers a floor space of 760 square meters and houses 29
ancient inscribed tablets dating back to the Han (206 B.C.-220)
and Wei (220-265) dynasties. The tablets reportedly bear the
earliest stone inscriptions in China.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition also includes 130 ancient inscribed tablets from
later dynasties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
