<HEADLINE> Yantai APEC High-Tech Industrial Park Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, October 11 (Xinhua) -- The Yantai Asia-Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) High-Tech Industrial Park was inaugurated over
the weekend in Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The high-tech industrial park is the fifth of its kind APEC
members have opened in China, following complexes in Beijing,
Xi'an, Hefei and Suzhou.
</P>
<P>
The new facility was established on the basis of the Yantai
High-Tech Industrial Development Zone founded in 1992 by
the city government. The State Council granted approval for APEC
members to open the zone earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
The high-tech industrial park will enjoy strong government
backing and various preferential policies granted to state-level
high-tech development zones.
</P>
<P>
The development zone has attracted some 200 enterprises in
recent years, including 80-odd foreign-funded ventures. Related
enterprises pumped some 1.5 billion yuan into fixed asset
investments between 1995-1997.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-five high-tech companies have produced products valued at
1.85 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Inauguration ceremonies were held in conjunction with the
Second APEC Small to Medium-Sized Enterprise Technology Exchange
Conference and Exhibition which opened in Yantai on October 8.
The exhibition will run through October 14.  
</P>
</TEXT>
