<HEADLINE> Fire Fighters Battle Forest Fire in Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Fire fighters backed by
helicopters were battling a raging forest fire near Israel's
northern port city of Haifa, Israel Radio reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of Haifa residents have been evacuated as strong
wind is carrying the fire in the Mountain Karmel, south of Haifa,
to the city.
</P>
<P>
Three people were slightly hurt by the fire strengthened by hot
and dry weather.
</P>
<P>
Two houses have been destroyed and four others seriously
damaged in one neighborhood of Haifa, the radio said. But other
reports said that at least 20 houses have been destroyed.
</P>
<P>
About 5,000 dunams (about 1,250 acres) of forest in the Karmel
national park have been burnt, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said the fire, which started in the early
morning, was caused by careless picnickers. But officials said
that arson remained a possibility. 
</P>
