<HEADLINE> Pakistan Pledges Smooth Staging of Hockey Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Hockey Federation
(PHF) chief Akhter Rasool Sunday promised that the pullout of
England will not influence the smooth staging of the Champions
Trophy hockey tournament to open on October 31 in Lahore.
</P>
<P>
England, who withdraw from the meet for alleged security
fears, was replaced by South Korea on account of their ranking in
the World Cup held in Holland in May.
</P>
<P>
Fears had been raised over the late laying of the turf in
Lahore, making it dangerous for the players.
</P>
<P>
Rasool dismissed the fear as unfounded and baseless, disputing
that the turf was laid in Holland a week before the world cup and
there were no injuries.
</P>
<P>
The poly grass turf reached Lahore a few days ago and the
laying process will start on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Defending champions Germany, world and Olympic champions
Holland, Commonwealth Games champions Australia, Spain as well as
hosts Pakistan are the other teams taking part in the twentieth
edition of the event.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan will be hosting the annual event for the 10th time,
initiated in 1978 by Pakistan itself with six top world teams
taking part. 
</P>
</TEXT>
