<HEADLINE> Trading Turnover in First 9 Months Rise at CSE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 11 (Xinhua) -- The trading turnover at the
Colombo Stock Exchange (CSE) rose by 6.7 percent during the first
9 months of this year compared with the same period last year,
according to the CSE monthly market report.
</P>
<P>
A turnover of 226.849 million U.S. dollars was recorded during
January-September, as against 212.703 Million U.S. dollars
registered a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the average daily turnover also rose to 1.274
million U.S. dollars from 1.188 million U.S. dollars. During the
period, 7.143 million U.S. dollars worth of shares were traded,
compared with the year-ago-level of 6.243 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
