<HEADLINE> Illegal Immigration Worst Headache of Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Illegal immigration is one of the
organized crimes disturbing Italy most, Italian Interior Minister
Giorgio Napolitano said Saturday in Trieste.
</P>
<P>
Napolitano made the remarks after some immigrant traffickers
dumped nine children, including three infants, into the sea
Saturday night in Puglia to divert police attention.
</P>
<P>
The children were then rescued by their parents, other adults
and the police patrol boat that was chasing the traffickers.
</P>
<P>
Napolitano made the incident public at a press briefing after
the first meeting of Interior Ministers from the 16 European
countries belonging to the Central European Initiative (CEL).
</P>
<P>
Italy's patrols along the Albanian coast are producing positive
results but "they are not sufficient," said the interior minister.
</P>
<P>
His government would urge Albania "to step-up its police checks
on departing Albanian boats and their owners which might be
attempting to ferry illegal immigrants," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
