<HEADLINE> Philippine President Starts State Visit to Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada left here Sunday for a four-day state visit to Singapore.
</P>
<P>
It is the president's first visit abroad since assuming office
on June 30 this year.
</P>
<P>
In his departure statement at Manila international airport,
Estrada said that he looks forward to laying down the foundation
for stronger bilateral relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
