partner of the Philippines," he said. "It has withstood the
current economic crisis in Asia in a remarkable manner because of
its sound fundamentals and strong institutions."
</P>
<P>
Estrada said that during the trip, he will enhance the
bilateral relations, especially the economic ties, between the two
countries and attract more investments into the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
President Estrada is set to meet with Singapore President Ong
Teng Cheong and Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong during his stay in
Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Singapore is the Philippines' third trade partner. Due to
disputes over the death by hanging of a Filipino maid in
Singapore, the two nations severed their relations in 1995 and
resumed formal ties early last year. 
