<P>
CANBERRA, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Australian Treasurer Peter
Costello Sunday indicated his government's intention to introduce
Goods and Services Tax (GTS) for the 2000 Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Costello said the coalition government, returning for a second
term in last weekend's election, planned to introduce a GST on
July 1, 2000, more than three months before the Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The plan upset the Sydney Olympics organizers.
</P>
<P>
Michael Knight, Olympics Minister for New South Wales state,
predicted a 110 million dollars (67 million U.S. dollars)
shortfall in the Games budget if the government went back on what
he said was a pledge to keep the sporting showpiece free of GST.
</P>
<P>
Knight said it would be extremely difficult to run the Games
if the exemption were not honoured. 
