<HEADLINE> Chongqing Increases Jobs for State Enterprise Laid-off Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, October 11 (Xinhua) -- The industrial center of
Chongqing Municipality in southwest China provided jobs for 85,000
laid-off workers from state-owned enterprises in the first nine
months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The Chongqing labor department estimates that the restructuring
of state-owned enterprises in the city over the next three years
will result in lay-offs for over 150,000 workers. The municipal
authorities consider the success of reemployment plans as key to
maintaining social stability.
</P>
<P>
By the end of September, about 2,000 local state enterprises
had set up reemployment centers designed to assist
132,000 laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
Early in June, a labor-market information network was set up and
has already helped over 3,000 laid-off workers to find new jobs. 
