<HEADLINE> hke101109 - Earthquake Rocks Palu in Indonesia's Central Sulawesi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 11 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring some
5.5 on the Richter scale hit Palu, capital of Indonesia's Central
Sulawesi, at dawn on Sunday, According to Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The Meteorology and Geophysics Body reported that the epicenter
was at some 16 kilometers northwest of Palu, or at the 0.8 of
south latitude and 119.8 of east longitude.
</P>
<P>
The quake had also led to a blackout in the city. Some office
buildings were cracked due to the jolt. But so far, there is no
victim reported.
</P>
<P>
Most of the inhabitants in Palu were still stayed out of their
houses as they were afraid of the next jolt, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, at least three tectonic quakes rocked
Palu, the biggest was on January 1, 1996, measuring at 7.2 at the
Richter scale. 
</P>
