<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Remote Sensing to Help Protect Scenic Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Advanced remote sensing
technology will help protect West Lake, the most famous scenic
site in east China's Zhejiang Province, according to the Hangzhou
Urban and Suburban Construction Committee.
</P>
<P>
West Lake has been selected as a test area which will be
administered with data provided by the urban geological
information system and remote sensing technology.
</P>
<P>
The system will enable the administration department closely
monitor the West Lake area and determine the most convenient
transportation routes for tourists. 
</P>
