<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Scientists to Conduct Gene Transfer in Space </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 10 (Xinhua) -- U.S. scientists from the
University of Wisconsin-Madison and Wisconsin Center for Space
Automation and Robotics will conduct on space shuttle Discovery to
be launched on October 29 an experiment whether microgravity can
provide a more efficient environment for gene transfer.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the university, U.S. scientists will
wrap about 1,000 soybean seedlings with water-soaked paper and
place them on the flight.
</P>
<P>
In a technique patented by the University of Toledo
researchers, the plants will have their meristem region damaged
just before launch. The meristem region directs the plant's
diverse growth of roots, stems and leaf cells.
</P>
<P>
This damaged area provides an entry point for the new genetic
information which can be incorporated into the plants. The genes
being introduced in this experiment has immune-strengthening
properties.
</P>
<P>
The process would allow use of soybean material as a source of
medicine to relieve arthritis symptoms.
</P>
<P>
The seedlings will be planted after they return to the ground
and researchers will monitor how many of them have the new trait.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981011.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Welcomes Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Enterprises from other part
of China opting to open new businesses in Guangzhou, the capital
of Guangdong Province, will enjoy the same treatment as local
firms in terms of taxation, fees, community service, access to
information, labor and personnel affairs as well as other areas.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government recent issued a 42-article document
clearly outlining related benefits as part of its effort to attract
outside investment.
</P>
<P>
The document stipulates that patented technology can represent
20 percent of registered capital, with patented high and new
technology evaluated as high as 60 percent.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises will also enjoy a number of other services and
preferential terms, including simplified registration procedures,
the opportunity to apply for foreign trade rights, participate in
overseas trade fairs and exchanges, and establish subsidiaries
abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
