<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peruvian, Bolivian Presidents to Meet in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- President of Peru Alberto Fujimori
and his Bolivian counterpart Hugo Banzer will meet here in
December to promote border development projects, official sources
said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents are expected to discuss a delayed road
project on their common border between the Peruvian port of Ilo
and the Bolivian capital city of La Paz, said Peruvian Ambassador
to Bolivia Harry Belevan.
</P>
<P>
Belevan said the delay in building the road has caused concern
to the authorities of both countries.
</P>
<P>
They will also discuss measures to regulate the waters of Lago
Titicaca on the border and ways to promote bilateral trade, which
has more than doubled in the recent years.
</P>
<P>
The two heads of state last met in May when President Fujimori
went to Bolivia to deliver aid relief to victims of the Cochabamba
earthquake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
