<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Reports Rise in Tax Revenue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's federal tax
revenue exceeded 8.6 billion U.S. dollars in September, up 8.7
percent over the same month of 1997, official reports said on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
However, Lytha Spindola, assistant secretary to the Federal
Tax Attorney, said less tax money was collected from certain
sectors, including the industry sector, because of sluggish
production activities.
</P>
<P>
The country's accumulated tax revenue between January and
September amounted to 86.48 billion dollars, a 25-percent increase
over the 69.1 billion dollars for the corresponding period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is expected to collect an estimated total of 101.694
billion dollars in tax this year, the assistant secretary said.
</P>
