<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Festina to Fight against Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Cycling sponsors Festina,
whose team were kicked out of this year's Tour de France over
drugs allegations, declared the plans to fight against doping on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The company will commit four million French francs (about
729,200 U.S. dollars) for research to beat doping, it was
announced on Saturday at the world road championships.
</P>
<P>
Festina are also to include a new clause in riders' contracts
that will give them the right to sack anyone caught using banned
products.
</P>
<P>
Their riders will also be given more rigorous medical checks
than the current blood tests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
