<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hartson Fined for Berkovic Kick </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 10 (Xinhua) -- West Ham striker John Hartson
was fined 10,000 pounds (17,110 U.S dollars) by the premier
league club on Saturday for kicking Israeli team mate Eyal
Berkovic in the head during training.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened last week and was captured on video and
screened worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The fine represents two weeks' wages for the Welsh
international and will be paid to a leukaemia charity.
</P>
<P>
"Despite Berkovic asking me not to fine Hartson that is what I
have done," said West Ham manager Harry Redknapp.
</P>
<P>
"John has apologised but he has still been fined the maximum
the Professional Footballers' Association will allow," he added.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday Hartson was fined 70 pounds (119.8 U.S. dollars) by
magistrates after he was captured on a security camera kicking a
flower pot in a Welsh town centre during a night out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
